<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
One new species was described (
<bibRefCitation author="Hausmann, A" journalOrPublisher="SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="241 - 247" refId="B5535948" refString="Hausmann, A, 2009. New and interesting geometrid moths from the Cape Verde Islands (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia 37: 241 - 247" title="New and interesting geometrid moths from the Cape Verde Islands (Lepidoptera: Geometridae)." volume="37" year="2009">Hausmann 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
After synonymising 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1925" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Aoshakuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aoshakuna" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Aoshakuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nipponogelasma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nipponogelasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev (2007)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nipponogelasma chlorissoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nipponogelasma chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Prout, 1913) to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microloxia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Microloxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5536812" refString="Leraut, P, 2009. Moths of Europe-Volume 2: Geometrid moths. NAP Editions, Paris" title="Moths of Europe-Volume 2: Geometrid moths." year="2009">Leraut (2009)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bubacek" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microloxia herbaria subsp. virideciliata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="herbaria" subSpecies="virideciliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Microloxia herbaria virideciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. h. subsp. herbaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="subSpecies" species="h." subSpecies="herbaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">M. h. herbaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hübner">Huebner</normalizedToken>
, 1813). 
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller, B" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5536891" refString="Mueller, B, Erlacher, S, Hausmann, A, Rajaei, H, Sihvonen, P, Skou, P, 2019. Volume 6. Part 1. Subfamily Ennominae II: (Boarmiini, Gnophini, additions to previous volumes). Brill, Leiden" title="Volume 6. Part 1. Subfamily Ennominae II: (Boarmiini, Gnophini, additions to previous volumes)." year="2019">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
et al. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
cited molecular and morphological evidence to justify elevating 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. h. subsp. virideciliata" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="subSpecies" species="h." subSpecies="virideciliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">M. h. virideciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
back to subspecies.
</paragraph>
